## 6. Color Usage Rules

### Primary Palette

| Color          | HEX       | Use                              |
| -------------- | --------- | -------------------------------- |
| Vibrant Orange | `#EF7215` | Calls-to-action, highlights      |
| Charcoal Black | `#0B0C0D` | Text, contrast sections          |
| Silver Gray    | `#D9D9D9` | Secondary backgrounds            |
| Light Gray     | `#F2F2F2` | Base backgrounds                 |
| Slate Gray     | `#456173` | UI elements, cards, neutral text |

### Complementary Palette

| Color         | HEX       | Use                   |
| ------------- | --------- | --------------------- |
| Electric Blue | `#00B0FF` | Buttons, icons, links |
| Teal Blue     | `#00796B` | Accents, hover states |

**Rules:**

- Use orange (`#EF7215`) for CTA and brand highlights.
- Use charcoal (`#0B0C0D`) for primary text.
- Use complementary blues to emphasize interaction.
- Maintain sufficient contrast for accessibility (WCAG AA+).

